1. *Peti* razred osnovne škole je veoma bitan za budućnost učenika. (*Fifth* grade of elementary school is very important for the future of students.) 

2. Moram *peti* stepenik da stignem do vrha. (I have to climb *fifth* step to reach the top.)

3. On je već *peti* put propustio čas engleskog. (He has already missed the *fifth* English class.)

4. *Peti* dan otkako nisam videla svoju najbolju prijateljicu. (*Fifth* day since I haven't seen my best friend.)

5. Sinoć sam se *peti* put u poslednjih mesec dana videla sa njim. (Last night was the *fifth* time I saw him in the last month.)

6. Njegov automobil može da razvije brzinu do *peti* km/h. (His car can reach speeds up to *fifth* km/h.)

7. Ona *peti* put pokušava da završi taj projekat. (She's trying to finish that project for the *fifth* time.)

8. Kada je stigao *peti* igrač na teren, ekipa je uspela da preokrene rezultat. (When the *fifth* player entered the field, the team managed to turn the score around.)

9. *Peti* element je pojam koji se koristi za objašnjenje stvari koje su izvan uobičajenog i poznatog. (*Fifth* element is a term used to explain things that are beyond the usual and known.)

10. Moraćemo da se *peti* uzbrdo kako bismo stigli do vidikovca. (We'll have to climb *up the fifth* hill to reach the viewpoint.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "peti" can be used in various forms, such as peti, petog, peti put, peti dan, peti element, peti igrač, peti razred, etc.